itemListElement.name: Only Wildlife and Whale Watching Tour Leaving from Seattle

name: Only Wildlife and Whale Watching Tour Leaving from Seattle
description:
*Get up close and personal with magnificent transient orcas, minke and humpback whales as well as harbor seal and an array of seabirds

*Soak in stunning mountain, island and ocean vistas as you cruise through the Salish Sea

*Perfect for a quick escape while staying in Seattle!

review.name: Graycful Whale Watching
review.reviewBody:
My 8 yr old son and I  went from Edmonds on a rather wet week day in early April to spot some Gray whales. And we were so privileged to spot a couple. Disappointed not to see orcas that day, but nature is unpredictable. We took a zip car from downtown Seattle as 25-30 mins away. Easy parking, comfortable vessel, great lunch and very welcoming and knowledgeable staff, with good on board resources to identify the whales.  Highly recommend this trip. 
To PSE - I wish the mug for life was a travel mug, so I could share the experience with all.

review.name: good 1/2 day activity
review.reviewBody: Great 1/2 day activity for all. Boat was very comfortable and has lunch and drink options for purchase. Lauren the on board Biologist was very knowledgeable and friendly. We saw seals, killing whales and an orca.

review.name: Whale watching tour
review.reviewBody:
I went on the wildlife and whale watching tour from Seattle, and it was such a fun and memorable experience! The boat was clean and comfortable, with great views from both inside and outside. The crew was friendly and shared lots of interesting facts about the animals we saw.  

We were lucky enough to spot a pod of orcas and a few humpback whales, which was absolutely incredible! We also saw sea lions, porpoises, and even a bald eagle. The scenery of the Puget Sound and the surrounding islands was stunning, making the trip even more special.  

This tour is perfect for anyone who loves nature or wants to see whales up close. I highly recommend it—it’s a must-do if you’re in Seattle!

review.name: Awesome tour
review.reviewBody: This a great tour to share with family and friends. Family friendly and educational. The crew was exceptional. Highly recommend

review.name: Convenient way to get out of the city.
review.reviewBody:
Had a good time out on the boat with this crew. Knowledgable about thge area and the geography. 
We enjoyed the fact that it wasn't too crowded. 

Great way to get out on the water if you want to get away from the city.

review.name: Prioritizing animal welfare regulations & educate humans about animals added to an awesome experience!!
review.reviewBody:
Relaxing day to enjoy sightseeing and being out in the water! I just wished we got to see more different whales and it would be cool to have the videos of them coming out of the water because they (the minke whales) were fast and it would have been cool to have that as a souvenir! It was also a little hard traveling solo because the seating up on the open decks get filled quickly and most people who had another person with them got to save their spot. There were a bunch of kids running around but I learned to shut them out and stayed in my own peaceful space lol. But it got cooler in the end and people eventually moved back to their assigned seats. I didn’t even sit in my assigned seat the whole time & when I went back to it in the very end, someone was sitting there. 
Overall, I absolutely enjoyed my time and I am glad we stayed out longer because we had to go out farther than usual to find them. I love seeing the birds & the harbor seals too! The tour guide speaker was very knowledgeable and I enjoyed the commentary during the trips and when/where to look. 
I was definitely looking forward to this tour because this was the reason why I booked the flight to Seattle and it was their last tour date of the season and I am so glad I made it! Although it was pricey & I would have paid premium to have the best seats, it somehow amended the tour option I got and maybe it’s because it was only for me. The kids getting a whale toy in the end is also cute that they cater to kids but it’s like paying for a sports event and the kids who know nothing about the sport are the ones getting the souvenir lol. Maybe it would help to borrow someone’s child next time to go with me jk lol. I still highly recommend this tour and I would definitely do this again and again! I will never get tired of watching animals! I also love that they follow the animal welfare guidelines and know that I am not contributing to harming any animals along the way. These animals are fascinating and this was such an amazing opportunity to see some animals & I already can’t wait until the next time.

review.name: Excellent tour!
review.reviewBody: Excellent tour and high safety standards! I did it as a solo traveler and photographer and I highly enjoyed it. We were able to encounter a family of 3 orcas, and some sea lions and seals. I really liked that the team of FRS Clipper chased the wildlife for us so we didn't miss the chance to see them. And I also loved all the facts they shared with us regarding these animals. In parallel , seeing those islands from afar was a delight. Highly recommended.

review.name: Excellent
review.reviewBody: The trip was great.. We were able to see the whales and other sea animals which we went for.  Good guide and boat.   Thanks to TripAdvisor

review.name: Ett måste i Seattle
review.reviewBody: Mycket fin båttur! Fick se både späckhuggare och knölval. Bra guide som gjorde resan extra trevlig. Café på båten som säljer enklare mat och dryck.

review.name: Problem with Trip Advisor/Viator.
review.reviewBody: I’m not rating the tour. We bought tickets for premium seating through trip advisor/viator. We got a call from FRS that the seats we purchased weren’t available and I was directed to call viator to change them. Unfortunately the call center wasn’t helpful and at this point, I have not received the email she promised showing the cancellation. Do not buy tickets directly thru trip advisor. Go to the website for FRS and get them directly.

name: Honeyhole Sandwiches
description: Best damn sandwiches in Seattle. We roast our own meats, make our sauces from scratch and have a full bar. Outdoor patio, private event room, and custom craft cocktails.

itemListElement.name: Downtown Seattle: Timeless Landmarks and Modern Sites with In-App Audio Tour

name: Downtown Seattle: Timeless Landmarks and Modern Sites with In-App Audio Tour
description:
Welcome to Seattle, a chief city of the state of Washington and a dynamic metropolis built on hills and around water.

There is a lot to do in Seattle, yet this audio tour will take you to the city's downtown and help you explore its history, legends, and architecture.

Witness how past and future masterfully intertwine in Seattle's architecture. Get to know the legend about the wishing chair and to whom it brings luck. See the first movie palace in the world that was opened in Seattle. Find the collective art project made of bubble gum of all flavors and colors. Learn where the remains of the original downtown are located.

The mobile app helps you explore Seattle with a private audio tour (included). All you need is a mobile phone. Download tours in advance to listen without WiFi.

The audio guide on the mobile app is the best way to enjoy the tour at your own pace. WeGoTrip app is available on the App Store and Google Play and works offline.

review.name: Audio gave a lot of information about the city and buildings.
review.reviewBody: At some points the directions seemed confusing.  Plus the walk took you up a very, very steep hill.  We had covered a similar area with another tour and there are ways to see all this without the huge hill.  Or even consider doing the tour in reverse so you are walking downhill instead of up.

itemListElement.name: Boat cruise in the shadow of Seattle

name: Boat cruise in the shadow of Seattle
description: Get a unique view of Seattle on a private yacht on Lake Union. This is a great way to see Seattle in a way that a bus or car tour cannot. Trips are customizable based on duration. These trips are 100% private and available for up to 6 people. You will not be mixed and matched with other clients (it will be your group and a USCG licensed captain of the vessel only). Feel free to ask the captain what your options are upon boarding and he will discuss the best way to maximize your trip. Feel free to bring food aboard and you can make it a meal on the water that very few people get the opportunity to enjoy. Again, please note that this service is available for 1-6 guests only per coast guard regulations. While the tour is outside in open air, if you wished to have a mask worn by the captain to help with any concerns related to COVID, they will be happy to wear a mask during the cruise.

itemListElement.name: Snoqualmie Falls, Historic Town & Wine Tasting in Wineries in Seattle Area

name: Snoqualmie Falls, Historic Town & Wine Tasting in Wineries in Seattle Area
description: This tour is unique in that you will be wine tasting at scenic wineries and experiencing beautiful landscapes such as a big waterfall, lake, forest, and a historic logging town with on old depot and exhibit of steam engines all in a half-day tour with a small group.

review.name: Shady and scary, big waste of money
review.reviewBody: One word: shady. She picked us up in a dilapidated old van that sounds like it's breaking down, the tour involved pointing out the window at trees along the freeway, and there was only one winery stop. Then a trip to the falls where we demanded she take us home. Nope, she refused. Instead drove us around for another hour. Seriously considered calling 911 at one point. Huge waste of money and time.

review.name: Not what you sign up for and overpriced
review.reviewBody:
We booked this tour because it said “wineries.” It’s safe to say the cost of $139 per person also gives the impression of a quality tour. That is not what we experienced. 
We were picked up in what felt like the guide’s personal vehicle, a dated Dodge Caravan. We were driven to Chateau Ste Michelle, which was the highlight of the 3.5 hrs we were with Susan, the tour guide. 
We still had to pay for the wine tasting, which is clear in the booking. We were then driven by other wineries but stopped at none. After some weird parking lot circles nearby the trek began to Snoqualmie Falls. Water and snacks were offered, as highlighted in the tour description, however the water was in plastic cups, not sealed bottles. The snacks were pulled out of a backpack and seemed like they came from the guide’s pantry. They were previously opened bags of pretzels, etc. which felt unsanitary and unsafe to us. We asked to be taken back to Seattle from the falls because we were annoyed and done but the guide still took us through her predetermined route. 
Had all this been communicated clearly in the tour description, and the price adjusted to max $30 per person, we would have no complaints. At this cost and only being taken to one winery, it is absurdly overpriced for what could be a cheaper Uber ride to and from your accommodations in Seattle. Save your money and drive yourself or Uber to the chateau.

review.name: Not what expected - but better!  Personalized, educational and enjoyable!
review.reviewBody: Was not what we expected but Suzanne was full of knowledge and took time to show us different wineries, natural wonders , and local history.  Would highly recommend if you are looking for something different and more personalized.

review.name: Wine tour
review.reviewBody:
We seemed rushed - from the beginning to the end.
I would do a private tour and go longer trip. We quickly saw the falls, drove through town , 1 winery stop did a tasting and drove around the parking lot at another winery and headed back.

review.name: Solo Traveler to Seattle
review.reviewBody:
This was a small group, only 2 of us plus the guide.  We only stopped at Chateau St Michele for a tasting.  The 4 wines we were brought in our tasting, neither of us cared for, but they didn't seem interested in helping us find wines we did enjoy.  Which both of us thought was odd, as we both drink wine.  We were also told that the day of our booking other wineries were closed, so I don't think they should book the tour if there aren't more options than 1 winery.  
On the up side, we were able to stop and pick fresh blackberries along the side of the road, which would not happen if you were in a large group.  We saw some beautiful sights.  
All in all, it was average, but probably not worth the price we paid.

review.name: A great experience
review.reviewBody:
Absolutely fabulous and well worth it.  Susan showed us so much that we would otherwise not know what to look for.  She was very knowledgeable about the areas and had a great passion for us as her guests.

Would 100% do this again.

itemListElement.name: Seattle's Civil War Legacy Walking Tour

name: Seattle's Civil War Legacy Walking Tour
description:
This unique tour teaches you about the unknown and forgotten Civil War history of Seattle's pioneers. 

Hear incredible tales of bravery on the battlefield and captivating stories of their postwar lives. Hear stories of men who fought at Gettysburg, marched to the Sea with Sherman, knew Abraham Lincoln or Susan B. Anthony, and escaped slavery to fight for their freedom. After all of that, they helped raise the young city of Seattle. 

Your guide will give a detailed, thorough and entertaining look back in history through the diverse stories of these amazing Civil War soldiers and their families.

review.name: So many goosebumps!
review.reviewBody:
My husband and I took a tour with Civil War Seattle on the last weekend of June. We learned so much about many Union soldiers buried in the Grand Army of the Republic Cemetery in Seattle. Little had we known their influence on the history of Seattle and on the healing of the different sides after the Civil War. Goosebumps ran up and down my arms as I listened to him unfold the lives of these men and their families in gripping detail. 

Thank you, Richard, for your knowledge and passion! Can't wait to take another tour with you.

description: Travel on Seattle's various transit choices, learn about the city, and learn how to get around! Travel on Seattle's various transit choices, learn about the city, and learn how to get around!

name: Seattle's Best Holiday Lights Tour
description:
Unlock the magic of the season with Tours Northwest on our 2-hour Seattle's Best Holiday Lights Tour! Learn the history behind your favorite holiday traditions while we make our way through local Seattle neighborhoods, showing off the best bright lights in the city. Let your festive guide show off the holiday spirit of downtown Seattle, Candy Cane Lane and more on this 2-hour tour.

Meeting Location: Westlake Center – 1624 4th Ave, Seattle, WA 98101.

Tour will depart from Westlake Center on 4th Avenue, in front of the Buffalo Wild Wings restaurant. Tour Guide will be next to coach dressed in festive attire. Please arrive 15 minutes early to check in.

review.name: Not worth the money.
review.reviewBody: Most of the 2 hour trip was sadly just driving.Well over an hour of just driving to see lights. Drove to the Olympic Manor neighborhood which was beautiful. We stopped at a Fred Mayer for a bathroom break. A group that was on the trip asked to be dropped back in town "anywhere"... We went back down town and dropped them off and another couple got off the tour van as well. Then we drove to the West Seattle neighborhood to see a single home. We were on this trip on Saturday 11/30. Maybe this is to early for lots of lights, not sure...

name: Secret Food Tours Seattle
description:
On our Secret Food Tour: Seattle you'll savor the extraordinary flavors of Pike Place Market. Your taste buds will be delighted with an array of local delights, featuring the iconic clam chowder and delightful local sweets.

Immerse yourself in the lively and joyful ambiance of this Picturesque Market, which stands as one of the USA's largest craft food markets. Here, you'll have the unique opportunity to meet dedicated local vendors and producers, gaining insight into the local culinary scene.

While navigating the bustling market lanes, we'll venture downstairs to the area known as the Downunder, providing you with a glimpse into the daily lives of the locals and the enduring traditions of North Pacific fishermen.

review.name: Good tour of Pike Place Market
review.reviewBody: Mary was an excellent tour guide who knew a lot of the history and significance of Pike Place Market. Food was good and Mary knew the history of each vendor we sampled from. This tour was not as extensive as one we did in Paris France but it was about half the  cost. No fault of the tour guide who did a superb job.

review.name: A Fun, Interesting Taste of Pike Place Market
review.reviewBody:
Our tour guide, Arty, texted us in the morning prior to our tour to verify meeting  place and time. There was a slight delay in starting the tour so Arty could help the other party meet up with us. We got a complete overview of the market including general Seattle history plus market history. We tasted some great local food and had a great time. Arty was very understanding of some of our walking limitations and did all he could to accommodate us and make sure we saw most everything. We can't wait to make another trip to explore the market more extensively on our own.
.

review.name: Great tour!
review.reviewBody: James is very personable and full of local tips and history. He made sure to point out things that we would have missed without even knowing it. Samples were very generous and everyone was great. Got a discount on purchases after the tour which was an unexpected bonus! Great tour!

review.name: Good
review.reviewBody:
Good tour. James was an excellent tour guide. The food didn't  blow me away, but the guided tour of the market was nice.

Things to know:
1. Bring water, otherwise you will get no drinks
2. Don't  expect to sit anywhere. Public seating is difficult to find and nowhere near the stops.
3. Don't  even think about acweekend tour if you want to actually move or breathe. Weekdays are even too crowded for me.

review.name: Secret food tour is fun and informative
review.reviewBody:
The Secret Food Tour showed us the lesser known gems of Pike Place Market. We tasted a variety of food including fruit, smoked salmon, clam chowder, cheese and chocolate cookies. All was delicious with Arty who is informative and fun.

Recommended to get the most out of the local food experience.

review.name: Secret Food Tour-Seattle
review.reviewBody:
James was an excellent guide-very knowledgeable. Great tour of the market and surrounding area.
We really enjoyed hearing about the history of the area as well.

review.name: Dia divertido em Seattle
review.reviewBody: Cidade muito interessante e bastante rica em detalhes e na cultura. A comida é demais e gostei da variedade que existe dentro do tour. Definitivamente é um passeio bem divertido

review.name: Yummy goodies and flying fish!
review.reviewBody: James was a wonderful tour guide. He shared his knowledge of the market and took us to some great shops. We enjoyed food goodies, too. Hubby even participated in catching a flying fish! It was well worth it, even on a cold January day!

review.name: Seattle food tour
review.reviewBody: Dominique was very educated on the area & courteous.  The food choices on the tour were excellent and well balanced.  Fun experience.

review.name: Good tour
review.reviewBody:
We took the Pike Place Market Tour on a  Friday.  The meeting point was easy to find and our guide, James, was waiting.  Once everyone arrived, we began the tour.  James is an excellent guide who has a great deal of knowledge about the Market and its history.

We stopped at a variety of market locations for food. It was all good.  A couple of the items were samples that were available to anyone walking by.  The most substantial portion was a turkey sandwich.  I didn't really understand this one.....it came from a bakery so the bread was good but it didn't really strike me as an item related to Seattle.

We enjoyed the tour and, again, James was great.  We recommend, especially if you've never been to the Market.

name: 2-Day Mt. Rainier National Park & Olympic National Park Tour from Seattle, WA
description:
1. Explore the tallest volcano of the continental United States
Go to Mt. Rainier to see the tallest volcano of the continental United States by visiting Christine Falls, Narada Falls, and Paradise Road.
2. Explore Olympic National Park, Crescent Lake & Seattle Ferry
We take you to visit Olympic National Park with visiting Hurricane Ridge, Lake Crescent and many other great wonders of the natural beauty.

Additional Notice:

1. The tour guide might change the duration for each stop depending on weather conditions or others.

2. The tickets fee should pay to the tour guide in cash and the tour guide will arrange activities admissions for the group. City Passes and Annual passes are not acceptable on our tours.

3. All meals and drinks during the trip are not included. The tour guide will provide eating suggestions.

name: Waterfall Wonderland Hike with Transport
description:
"The mountains are calling and I must go." ~ John Muir

If you've ever felt the pull of the mountains or a need to get into nature - we get you. We feel the pull every day which is why we wanted to create an opportunity to share the beauty and experience of nature with you. 

We know that each person is different - perhaps the roar of a waterfall soothes your soul. Or the quiet stillness of the deep forest brings you peace. Or perhaps you love the physical challenge of the trail. 

You traveled to Seattle because you heard stories of it's beauty - of the land and water. We take care to craft the perfect hike that will be the highlight of your trip. Wallace Falls is a delicate balance of the awesome power of water that helped carve the landscape, and the peacefulness of our Washington forests full of ferns and moss.

review.name: Fantastic hike and fantastic guide!
review.reviewBody: Loved this tour with Sophia!  She is an amazing guide and took great care of us.  She supplied light breakfast, snacks, lunch, drinks, sunscreen, backpacks, and trekking poles.  The 6 mile hike is definitely moderate but we loved the challenge.  The views of the falls are stunning.  So beautiful! Highly recommend this adventure and this tour company!

name: Pacific Northwest Peaks & Pours
description: On this 8-day journey, experience the Pacific Northwest’s unrivaled beauty: spectacular waterfalls, magnificent mountains, young, vibrant cities—and some of the most imaginative craft beers in the country. American Experiences small group, multi-day tours provide you with authentic, in-depth experiences not found elsewhere. Your trip includes more than just the basics-- a welcome reception, one or two unique specialty meals, three and four star quality boutique hotels, multiple guided tours with opportunities to choose your activity as well as free independent exploration, and transportation. Plus, our knowledgeable tour guide stays with you for the duration of the trip and can personalize your experiences to meet the needs of both you and the group. Get to know like-minded people from all over the world who enjoy similar experiences and enrich your appreciation of America's special Pacific Northwest with American Experiences small group tours. It's not just a tour, it's an Experience!

itemListElement.name: Scandals, Ghosts & Oddities at Pike Place Market

name: Scandals, Ghosts & Oddities at Pike Place Market
description:
Pike Place Market has had a long and scandalous history that includes brothels, coffee shops, Chief Seattle, and mischievous ghosts. Come join me to hear the market's stories, and explore the market.

Pike Place Market is the heart of Seattle. The market is nine acres packed with local farmers, artists, wineries, buskers, specialty businesses and fish being thrown. I have extensive experience being a market tour guide and I am a retired chef. My goal is to get my guests familiar with the market layout, vendors, foods and history.

review.name: Fun and informative!
review.reviewBody: Informative and fun! A touch of sass mixed with historical accounts.  The group was friendly and willing to listen. The Native stories were heartbreaking and need to be heard.

review.name: If you only have time for one tour of Seattle do this one!
review.reviewBody: In town for a very brief visit and this was the tour that suited my timeframe and interests. It did not disappoint Carolyn is a treasure trove of stories, facts and practical advice for tourists. Really enjoyed the stories of Seattle - it is such an interesting historic city.

review.name: Our Guide, Carolyn, was awesome!
review.reviewBody: My wife and I had a great time. Our guide, Carolyn, was wonderful. She was very knowledgeable and so very pleasant. She took her time and shared so many interesting facts about the market. She took us places we had no idea existed. It was a great time!

review.name: Pre cruise city tour
review.reviewBody:
Very informative and enlightening tour of the Market and the history of it 
Highly recommend it 
Tour guide was delightful

review.name: Highly recommend!
review.reviewBody: This was such a fun way to see the Market. Carolyn is your friend from the minute you meet her. You can tell she loves the stories, history and her community. I learned so much and now feel like a bit of an insider now as I walk through the market.

review.name: Thoroughly enjoyable
review.reviewBody: Thoroughly enjoyable tour. Carolyn was really knowledgeable and super interesting. She has lots of local knowledge and weird and wonderful facts. I was on my own and she was very friendly and warm. Would definitely recommend.

review.name: A REALLY GREAT TIME.
review.reviewBody: This was a wonderful experience, and so much fun.  I was part of a great group of people, none who I knew, but with Carolyn we became fast friends.  Great stories, great history behind the stories.  Carolyn has a way of keeping you engaged with every tail and with every turn there is another mystery to discover.  I highly recommend her tour.

review.name: Unusual historical information made fun !
review.reviewBody: Excellent tour !  Carolyn was very knowledgeable and presented information in an interesting way.  She packed in a lot of information in a short time but made it fun and casual.  We really enjoyed the tour and recommend it highly.

review.name: Do this!!
review.reviewBody: Fun and entertaining tour! Carolyn is a font of historical information and current trends in the city. Thoroughly enjoyed!!

review.name: The perfect insider's guide to Pike Place Market
review.reviewBody: What a perfect way to complete our day discovering new places in Seattle! Carolyn's tour was definitely the icing on the cake. I love how she wove the interesting history in the wonderful sights and sounds of Pike Place market. Especially interesting was the history of the vendors of the market, how they take care of each other, what the best spots are, more things we are able to do on our own, and how Pike Place was integral in the formation of Seattle itself, along with famous area businesses. Carolyn's knowledge of the vendors was also appreciated - it gave us an "inside" to the people and area. She's obviously on great terms with the vendors, and that closeness made it a better experience for all of us. Plus, as a former James Beard award winning chef, she knows food, and gave advice on the best places to grab a bite. Thank you for the fun afternoon!

itemListElement.name: PROFi DRIVER Seattle, Washington, United States

name: PROFi DRIVER Seattle, Washington, United States
Morning Mimosa Sail
description: Start your day with a Morning Mimosa sail aboard our Benetea Oceanis 35! There’s no better way to start your day in Seattle than sailing in the gentle morning light, past stunning sights, while sipping a cool Mimosa!
